**Your New Company**\
Mackellar is the mining services contractor for Bravus' Carmichael Mine,
partnering to deliver long-term employment and opportunities across
regional Queensland. While our main recruitment hubs are Townsville and
Rockhampton, we encourage applications from all regional Queensland
communities.\
\
**Your New Role**\
In this role, you will lead production crews within a fast-paced coal
mining environment, ensuring operations are carried out safely and
efficiently. Key responsibilities include:

-   Leading and supervising production crews to achieve daily safety and
    production targets

-   Promoting and upholding the Site Safety Health Management System,
    environmental plans, and all statutory requirements

-   Driving operational performance and continuous improvement

-   Facilitating and participating in pre-starts and safety meetings

-   Building, coaching and supporting high-performing teams

-   Monitoring production results and maintaining accurate operational
    records

**Why Mackellar**

-   Permanent position on a long-term project with a strong development
    pipeline

-   Attractive salary and a 7/7 rotating roster supporting genuine
    work--life balance

-   Paid FIFO from Townsville or Rockhampton

-   Camp, pit and airport all within 5 minutes -- minimal travel time

-   Fully catered accommodation village with gym and recreational
    facilities

**What You'll Need to Succeed**

-   Current Standard 11 and Mining Supervisor competencies (G1, G2, G8,
    G9)

-   Proven leadership experience in an open cut mining environment

-   Strong knowledge of WHS legislation and statutory obligations

-   A flexible, solutions-focused mindset with the ability to adapt to
    change

-   Excellent communication skills and a demonstrated ability to mentor
    and develop others

-   A strong commitment to safety with a history of positive safety
    outcomes

-   Competent user of Microsoft Office Suite

*Only candidates who meet the required experience and qualifications
will be contacted.*
